! Wye-delta (Yd) three-phase transformer power-flow comparison case.
! (BMOPF subtype: wye_delta)
!
! Topology: hv ──[Yd xfmr, 11 kV wye / 0.415 kV delta]── lv
!   hv.1/2/3/4  = HV wye phases and neutral
!   lv.1/2/3    = LV delta terminals (no neutral on delta bus)
!
! Design intent for high-confidence cross-validation:
!
!   (a) Series impedance is load-bearing:
!       %r=1.0 per winding, xhl=4.0% → at 75% rated load the HV-winding
!       series drop is ≈ (0.01+j0.04)×0.75×242 Ω × I, giving several volts
!       on the LV side — well above the 0.1 V comparison tolerance.
!
!   (b) No-load shunt is exercised:
!       %noloadloss=0.3 %imag=1.5 → core loss ≈ 1.5 kW, magnetising
!       current ≈ 7.5 A (HV), both visible in the KCL balance.
!
!   (c) Load unbalance is large enough to expose per-phase constraint errors:
!       Loads in ratio 3:1:2 across the three delta phases → inter-phase
!       LV voltage spread of several volts.  A wrong sign on any one phase
!       in the Yd voltage loop would shift that phase by >1 V (detectable).
!
! Total load ≈ 375 kW + 120 kvar (≈ 75 % of rated at 0.95 pf).

Clear

New Circuit.pf_yd_xfmr basekv=11.0 pu=1.0 angle=0 phases=3 bus1=hv.1.2.3 model=ideal

! HV wye neutral earthed via near-zero reactor.
New Reactor.grnd_hv bus1=hv.4 bus2=hv.0 R=0.001 X=0

! 2-winding WYE-DELTA transformer with realistic losses.
New Transformer.t1 phases=3 windings=2
~ wdg=1 bus=hv.1.2.3.4 conn=wye   kv=11.0  %r=1.0 kva=500
~ wdg=2 bus=lv.1.2.3   conn=delta kv=0.415 %r=1.0 kva=500
~ xhl=4.0
~ %noloadloss=0.3
~ %imag=1.5

! High-impedance grounding on one LV delta terminal to anchor the floating
! common mode without materially affecting the power flow (1 MΩ → ~0.23 mA).
New Reactor.grnd_lv bus1=lv.1 bus2=lv.0 R=1e6 X=0

! Balanced constant-power phase-to-phase loads on the LV delta bus.
! Equal loads on each delta arm: symmetry forces the LV common mode to zero
! in both ODS and BMOPF, making phase-to-earth comparison valid.
! Vminpu=0 Vmaxpu=2: disable ODS voltage-dependent load switching so model=1
! behaves as strict constant P+Q at all voltages, matching BMOPF.
New Load.ld1 bus1=lv.1.2 kv=0.415 kw=120 kvar=40 phases=1 model=1 Vminpu=0 Vmaxpu=2
New Load.ld2 bus1=lv.2.3 kv=0.415 kw=120 kvar=40 phases=1 model=1 Vminpu=0 Vmaxpu=2
New Load.ld3 bus1=lv.3.1 kv=0.415 kw=120 kvar=40 phases=1 model=1 Vminpu=0 Vmaxpu=2

Set VoltageBases=[11.0, 0.415]
CalcVoltageBases
Solve
